value.value: A subjective score of 4 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
A subjective score of 5 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
A subjective score of 6 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
This gene plays a role in interleukin signaling, immunity and inflammation.
A subjective score of 7 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
A subjective score of 8 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
A subjective score of 9 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
A subjective score of 10 on a scale that ranges from 0: No undesired sedation at all to 10: undesired sedation as bad as it can be.
Human IL23R wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1p31.3 and is approximately 121 kb in length. This allele, which encodes interleukin-23 receptor, is involved in immune cell activation.

A derivative of the Canarypox Virus, ALVAC can infect mammalian cells but it can't replicate.  Thus, it produces a self-limiting infection which does not produce symptoms or harm the host.  When carrying foreign genes it will cause transient expression of protein.
Interleukin-23 receptor (629 aa, ~72 kDa) is encoded by the human IL23R gene. This protein plays a role in JAK-STAT signaling and immune cell activation.
A brain glioblastoma that occurs during childhood.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of the ABCD1 gene.

label.value: Number of Lymph Nodes with Micrometastases

value.value: The number of examined lymph nodes that were positive for micrometastases.

label.value: Number of Lymph Nodes with Macrometastases

value.value: The number of examined lymph nodes that were positive for macrometastases.
Use of a test strip designed to detect one or more specific substances in urine. Results are indicated by a color change and may be qualitative or semi-quantitative.
An oropharyngeal squamous cell carcinoma which is negative for p16INK4a by immunohistochemistry. This negative immunohistochemistry result does not exclude human papillomavirus infection.
An immunohistochemistry test result indicating that the neoplastic cells are negative for p16INK4a antibody in a tissue sample.
Any agent that can alter hormone levels or modulate hormone effects.
Guidelines for monitoring and reporting vascular thrombosis response. These guidelines are consistent with RECIST1.1 and consider thrombosis as a non-measurable disease.
Complete resolution of thrombosis, with recanalization of vessel.

Any of a) partial recanalization of thrombosis (if prior complete blockage), b) unequivocal reduction in the maximal girth of thrombosis, c) unequivocal reduction in the volume, or elimination, of arterial enhancing portion of thrombosis.

Any unequivocal, unambiguous increase in the volume of new or existing enhancing thrombosis. Unequivocal progression of thrombosis corresponds to at least 73% increase in volume, which is similar to 20% increase in diameter, and at least a 5 mm absolute increase.

Any of a) no change or small changes that do not meet the criteria for irPR or irPD, taking as reference the smallest sum diameters while on study, b) increase in the volume of non-enhancing thrombosis, c) new bland non-enhancing thrombosis.
A plan of action intended to accomplish a specific goal.
A modification of the Nottingham grading system for use in grading breast carcinoma.
A low combined histologic grade (favorable), SBR score of 3-5 points.
An intermediate combined histologic grade (moderately favorable), SBR score of 6-7 points.
A high combined histologic grade (unfavorable), SBR score of 8-9 points.
An anatomic site that is not specified or defined well enough to associate with a specific site.
A finding indicating that chronic lymphocytic leukemia does not respond to treatment with Bruton's tyrosine kinase (BTK) inhibitor, ibrutinib.
Any agent that inhibits the activity of the enzyme CYP17A1.

label.value: Advanced Lung Non-Squamous Non-Small Cell Carcinoma

value.value: Non-squamous non-small cell lung carcinoma that has spread extensively to other anatomic sites or is no longer responding to treatment.

label.value: Allogeneic Hematopoietic Stem Cell Transplant Recipient

value.value: A person receiving an allogeneic hematopoietic stem cell transplant.
A protein encoded by the AMHR2 gene.

label.value: Anti-Muellerian Hormone Type-2 Receptor Extracellular Domain

value.value: Anti-Muellerian hormone type-2 receptor extracellular domain is encoded by the human AMHR2 gene. This protein may play a role in ovarian carcinogenesis.
This gene plays a role in the negative regulation of appetite.

Human CARTPT wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 5q13.2 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes cocaine- and amphetamine-regulated transcript protein, is involved in the regulation of appetite.
Cocaine- and amphetamine-regulated transcript protein (116 aa, ~13 kDa) is encoded by the human CARTPT gene. This protein plays a role in the inhibition of appetite.
This gene may be involved in the regulation of gene expression.

Human DUX4L2 gene is located in the vicinity of 4q35.2 and is approximately 1 kb in length. This allele, which encodes double homeobox protein 4-like protein 2, may play a role in transcription. This gene is within a D4Z4 repeat array; contraction of this macrosatellite repeat is associated with facioscapulohumeral muscular dystrophy (FSHD).
Double homeobox protein 4-like protein 2 (424 aa, ~45 kDa) is encoded by the human DUX4L2 gene. This protein may be involved in transcriptional regulation.
This gene plays a role in retinoid acid-independent G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

Human GPRC5D wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p13.1 and is approximately 39 kb in length. This allele, which encodes G-protein coupled receptor family C group 5 member D, is involved in G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

label.value: G-Protein Coupled Receptor Family C Group 5 Member D

value.value: G-protein coupled receptor family C group 5 member D (39 aa, ~39 kDa) is encoded by the human GPRC5D gene. This protein plays a role in G protein-coupled receptor signaling.
